the New York Times SERIES list at #1 with A Court of Wings and Ruin!','http://books.google.com/books/content?id=4fZaEAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','2026-03-15 06:58:31','4fZaEAAAQBAJ',NULL,'Bloomsbury Publishing USA',2018,'Fiction','NOT_MATURE','0.1.2.0.preview.1',739),(1165,NULL,'How Well Do You Know A Court of Thorns and Roses (ACOTAR)?','Selene Riddlemoon','How Well Do You Know the A Court of Thorns and Roses Series? Calling all fans of the ACOTAR series! Are you ready to put your knowledge of the Court of Thorns and Roses to the ultimate test? Whether you\'re a die-hard fan who\'s read every book in the ACOTAR book set or a newcomer diving into the world of Feyre, Tamlin, and Rhysand, this quiz is for you! This is your chance to prove you know every twist, turn, and trial from the A Court of Thorns and Roses series, including A Court of Mist and Fury and beyond. From the enchanted lands of the Spring Court to the mysterious depths of the Night Court, the Court of Thorns and Roses series will test the limits of your memory. Do you remember every detail from each book in the A Court of Thorns and Roses series set? Do you know all the secrets behind the courts, the characters, and their complex relationships? In this ACOTAR quiz, you\'ll face questions that challenge your understanding of the world Sarah J. Maas has created. From Feyre\'s transformation to the epic journeys across the lands, each question brings you closer to proving you\'re a true fan of the A Court of Thorns and Roses universe. So, are you ready to take the test and see how well you really know the Court of Thorns and Roses? Take the 100-question challenge now, and get ready to dive deep into the magic, mystery, and romance of one of the most beloved fantasy series of our time!','http://books.google.com/books/content?id=0NCR0QEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','2026-03-15 06:58:31','0NCR0QEACAAJ','Can You Pass These 100-Question Challenge?','Independently Published',2025,'Fiction','NOT_MATURE','preview-1.0.0',0),(1166,'1635577756','A Court of Thorns and Roses eBook Bundle','Sarah J. Maas','Passionate, violent, sexy and daring ... A true page-turner - USA TODAY on A Court of Thorns and Roses Feyre is a huntress. The skin of a wolf would bring enough gold to feed her sisters for a month. But the life of a magical creature comes at a steep price, and Feyre has just killed the wrong wolf ... Follow Feyre\'s journey into the dangerous, alluring world of the Fae, where she will lose her heart, face her demons, and learn what she is truly capable of. This four-ebook bundle of the #1 New York Times bestselling series by Sarah J. Maas includes A Court of Thorns and Roses, A Court of Mist and Fury, A Court of Wings and Ruin, and the companion tale A Court of Frost and Starlight.','http://books.google.com/books/content?id=nYgHEAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','2026-03-15 06:58:31','nYgHEAAAQBAJ','A 4 Book Bundle','Bloomsbury Publishing USA',2020,'Fiction','NOT_MATURE','1.6.6.0.preview.3',2974),(1167,'1984806742','Beach Read','Emily Henry','FROM THE #1 NEW YORK TIMES BESTSELLING AUTHOR OF FUNNY STORY! A romance writer who no longer believes in love and a literary writer stuck in a rut engage in a summer-long challenge that may just upend everything they believe about happily ever afters. As featured in The New York Times Book Review ∙ Entertainment Weekly ∙ Oprah Magazine ∙ Betches ∙ Shondaland ∙ Good Morning America ∙ The New York Post ∙ Good Housekeeping ∙ CNN ∙ and more! Augustus Everett is an acclaimed author of literary fiction. January Andrews writes bestselling romance. When she pens a happily ever after, he kills off his entire cast. They’re polar opposites. In fact, the only thing they have in common is that for the next three months, they\'re living in neighboring beach houses, broke, and bogged down with writer\'s block. Until, one hazy evening, one thing leads to another and they strike a deal designed to force them out of their creative ruts: Augustus will spend the summer writing something happy, and January will pen the next Great American Novel. She’ll take him on field trips worthy of any rom-com montage, and he’ll take her to interview surviving members of a backwoods death cult (obviously). Everyone will finish a book and no one will fall in love. Really.','http://books.google.com/books/content?id=lxGuDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','2026-03-15 06:59:35','lxGuDwAAQBAJ',NULL,'Penguin',2020,'Fiction','NOT_MATURE','2.7.6.0.preview.2',401),(1169,'1602355479','Florida','Jeff Rice','This collection proposes Florida as a nexus of various contested moments, ideas, concepts, and relations. In the age of networks, it is not enough to only think of computerized, economic, or labor-intensive systems as networks. Florida is both a site of exploration—what does Florida mean – and a model for spatial work in general—how do we trace out the networked connections of a given space? Florida taps into an existing conversation regarding space, and it contributes a new approach by offering up the state as a network of both objective and personal meanings.','http://books.google.com/books/content?id=QasWEAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','2026-03-15 06:59:35','QasWEAAAQBAJ',NULL,'Parlor Press LLC',2015,'Computers','NOT_MATURE','0.1.1.0.preview.2',275),(1170,'0996294120','Sea-Devil','Jessica Sherry','You never forget your first love. Or your first murder. Escaping her mistake-ridden past, smart and sassy book nerd Delilah Duffy returns to the island she adored as a child to reinvent herself as the manager of Beach Read, a local bookstore. With disturbing acts of vandalism following her every step, the message is clear—she’s not welcome. Tensions escalate when a chilling murder stains the floors of her bookstore on the eve of her grand opening, and she’s quickly pegged as the prime suspect. With questions left unanswered and suspicion high, even from her family, one person stands by her—local cop Sam Teague, her first love and most devastating heartbreak. His kindness and support are an unexpected lifeline if she can trust it. He helps her see her own potential, but she can’t forget the pain he once caused. He broke her heart once—she can’t let it happen again. With evidence mounting against her, Delilah must use her head and her heart to clear her name before the killer strikes again, even if it means confronting her past and trusting the one who left her broken.','http://books.google.com/books/content?id=jHezEAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','2026-03-15 06:59:35','jHezEAAAQBAJ','A Delilah Duffy Mystery','Jessica Sherry',2015,'Fiction','NOT_MATURE','1.22.20.0.preview.3',360),(1171,'9781930006508','Rhoades To Reading Fourth Edition, Level I Teaching Guide','Jacqueline Rhoades','Reading program for 5th grade - adult students. Instruction level K-2.5. Includes 340 sight words, vowel and consonant sounds, sound blending, consonant-vowel consonant words, beginning and ending blends, silent e rule, three letter clusters, cursive handwriting, 115 activity sheets and 6 stories.','http://books.google.com/books/content?id=5zKAr4Z8ni4C&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','2026-03-15 06:59:35','5zKAr4Z8ni4C',NULL,'The Reading Company',2004,'Language Arts & Disciplines','NOT_MATURE','1.9.13.0.preview.1',304),(1172,'1950654532','Beach Read Boxed Set','Marie Force','Welcome to this new Beach Read Boxed Set, containing nine of my single title contemporary romances, all of which have been reader favorites! Here you’ll find everything from steamy couples in Marfa, Texas, to an unlucky-in-love super model to a prominent doctor who falls in love with his best friend’s girlfriend to a woman putting her life back together after the death of her mother to a young couple separated by tragedy but brought back together by love. Each title offers a sizzling love story and a guaranteed happy ending. So get comfortable and be prepared to fall in love—nine times!','http://books.google.com/books/content?id=brUAEAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','2026-03-15 06:59:35','brUAEAAAQBAJ',NULL,'HTJB, Inc.',2020,'Fiction','NOT_MATURE','1.2.2.0.preview.2',3001),(1173,NULL,'The Delilah Duffy Mystery Series Boxset','Jessica Sherry','Running a successful bookstore in a small seaside town can be murder! Meet Delilah Duffy. A gutsy but error-prone book nerd starting over as manager of Beach Read Books on the island she loved as a child and hoping to disappear into the anonymous folds of a small tourist town. But home to her flighty Duffy relatives and first love and heartbreak, Sam Teague, her second chance is no vacation. When a murder happens the night before her grand opening, Delilah must unravel the mystery to save herself and her business, propelling her into an unexpected role as an amateur sleuth. Follow Delilah’s puzzling cases in this five-book series as she battles murderers, arsonists, thieves, and her high anxiety in her ultimate quest for love, family, and a quiet beach life. Get the small-town mystery and romance series that readers describe as “funny,” “thrilling,” and “suspenseful.”','http://books.google.com/books/content?id=ysrfEAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','2026-03-15 06:59:35','ysrfEAAAQBAJ',NULL,'Jessica Sherry',2023,'Fiction','NOT_MATURE','1.13.11.0.preview.2',1244),(1174,'0996294139','Luna-Sea: A Delilah Duffy Mystery','Jessica Sherry','We’re all just one pain away from lunacy. Book lover and amateur sleuth Delilah Duffy returns in her second thrilling adventure. With her bookstore open and her sweet romance with Sam deepening, Delilah’s finally won the quiet, small-town life she wants, or so it seems. Nothing’s easy, not with continued business woes and leftover trauma from her last case adding to the chaos. A fancy party at the luxurious Peacock Inn should be a pleasant distraction, but when the party takes an eerie turn, Delilah discovers another mystery – she thinks. Her anxiety disorder intensifies, and with no evidence to prove her claims, she can\'t be sure of anything. Even her relationship with Sam feels strained with secrets. Not one to back down from a challenge, Delilah’s desperate search for the truth soon lands her in trouble with a ruthless criminal ring. Danger lurks around every corner, and she must use all her wits to uncover the truth and take down the lunatic masterminding it all. With her business on the line and her romance with Sam at stake, will Delilah be able to solve the mystery in time, or will this be the end of the cozy life she\'s worked so hard to build? ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ “I loved Luna Sea! Delilah Duffy is such a great character, strong willed and smart. But her impulsive side is what keeps me interested! I love when she gets herself in trouble!” ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ “… if you like a light read with some humor, some fear, some violence and some sweet love, well, you have it all with this book.” ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ “It\'s also great to see a character who is fighting her personal demons and able to work through them with the help of a loving and supportive partner. I\'m really enjoying this series and can\'t wait for the next installment!”','http://books.google.com/books/content?id=NqOzEAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','2026-03-15 06:59:35','NqOzEAAAQBAJ',NULL,'Jessica Sherry',2015,'Fiction','NOT_MATURE','0.18.19.0.preview.3',354),(1175,'1250256895','Hello, Summer','Mary Kay Andrews','New York Times bestselling author and Queen of the Beach Reads Mary Kay Andrews delivers her next blockbuster, Hello Summer. It’s a new season... Conley Hawkins left her family’s small town newspaper, The Silver Bay Beacon, in the rearview mirror years ago. Now a star reporter for a big-city paper, Conley is exactly where she wants to be and is about to take a fancy new position in Washington, D.C. Or so she thinks. For small town scandals... When the new job goes up in smoke, Conley finds herself right back where she started, working for her sister, who is trying to keep The Silver Bay Beacon afloat—and she doesn’t exactly have warm feelings for Conley. Soon she is given the unenviable task of overseeing the local gossip column, “Hello, Summer.” And big-time secrets. Then Conley witnesses an accident that ends in the death of a local congressman—a beloved war hero with a shady past. The more she digs into the story, the more dangerous it gets. As an old heartbreaker causes trouble and a new flame ignites, it soon looks like their sleepy beach town is the most scandalous hotspot of the summer.','http://books.google.com/books/content?id=LZmyDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','2026-03-15 06:59:35','LZmyDwAAQBAJ','A Novel','St. Martin\'s Press',2020,'Fiction','NOT_MATURE','1.16.15.0.preview.2',526),(1176,NULL,'Torreya',NULL,NULL,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=a8gwAQAAMAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','2026-03-15 06:59:35','a8gwAQAAMAAJ',NULL,NULL,1903,'Botany','NOT_MATURE','3.6.6.0.full.1',668),(1177,'1649377371','Fourth Wing','Rebecca Yarros','As war grows more deadly, Violet Sorrengail joins the elite Navarre: the dragon riders. But she\'ll need to keep her wits because once you enter the Basgiath War College, there are only two ways out: graduate or die.','http://books.google.com/books/content?id=kU8ZEQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','2026-03-15 07:00:27','kU8ZEQAAQBAJ',NULL,'Entangled: Red Tower Books',2024,'Fiction','NOT_MATURE','preview-1.0.0',0),(1178,NULL,'Summary of Onyx Storm by Rebecca Yarros','Insight Reads Press ','DISCLAIMER: This is an unofficial summary and analysis guide. This is NOT the original book by Rebecca Yarros. For the complete original novel, please purchase \"Onyx Storm\" by Rebecca Yarros. Unlock the Secrets of Onyx Storm with This Comprehensive Summary Guide! Struggling to keep track of the epic twists, heart-wrenching character arcs, and complex world-building in Rebecca Yarros\'s Onyx Storm? This detailed summary guide is your ultimate companion to the third installment of the bestselling Empyrean series. What You\'ll Discover: ✅ Complete Chapter-by-Chapter Breakdown – Navigate the intricate plot from Violet\'s desperate quest to save Xaden to the shocking twelve-hour memory gap that changes everything ✅ In-Depth Character Analysis – Explore Violet Sorrengail\'s evolution from student to duchess, Xaden Riorson\'s tragic venin transformation, and the development of beloved supporting characters like Ridoc, Rhiannon, Sawyer, and more ✅ World-Building Explained – Understand the expansion beyond Basgiath War College to the mysterious southern isles, the seventh breed of dragons (irids), and the failing Aretian wards ✅ Central Themes & Symbolism – Discover the deeper meanings behind love and sacrifice, power and responsibility, trust and betrayal that drive this epic fantasy romance ✅ Writing Style Analysis – Learn what makes Rebecca Yarros\'s distinctive voice so compelling, from her emotive prose to her masterful pacing techniques ✅ Critical Analysis & Reader Reception – Get balanced perspectives on the book\'s strengths and weaknesses, comparisons to Fourth Wing and Iron Flame, and what critics are saying ✅ Fan Theories Explored – Dive into the most popular theories about Xaden\'s \"new brother,\" the Naolin-Berwyn connection, and what\'s coming in Book 4 ✅ What\'s Next for the Series – Prepare for the upcoming fourth book with insights into timeline expectations, confirmed plot points, and speculation about the series finale Perfect For: Readers who want to refresh their memory before Book 4 releases Book club members preparing for discussions Fans who need help understanding complex plot points and character relationships Busy readers who want to stay current with the series Anyone looking to deepen their appreciation of the Empyrean world This comprehensive guide includes: 7 detailed chapters covering every aspect of Onyx Storm Analysis of major plot points, character arcs, and thematic elements Comparisons to previous books in the series Exploration of symbolism and narrative techniques Reader reactions and critical reception The most popular fan theories and speculation Whether you\'ve just finished Onyx Storm and need help processing that devastating cliffhanger, or you\'re preparing to dive into the book and want a companion guide, this summary provides everything you need to fully appreciate Rebecca Yarros\'s epic fantasy romance. Discover why millions of readers are obsessed with the Empyrean series. Get your copy today and master the storm! IMPORTANT DISCLAIMER: This book is a summary, analysis, and companion guide created to enhance your understanding and appreciation of \"Onyx Storm\" by Rebecca Yarros. It is not affiliated with, authorized, or endorsed by Rebecca Yarros, her publishers, or any related entities. This is NOT a replacement for the original book. To experience the full story, characters, and Rebecca Yarros\'s complete narrative, please purchase the official \"Onyx Storm\" novel. All character names, places, and story elements are the property of Rebecca Yarros and her publishers. This guide is intended for educational and informational purposes only. Onyx Storm summary, Rebecca Yarros, Empyrean series, Fourth Wing series, dragon fantasy, fantasy romance summary, book analysis, Violet Sorrengail, Xaden Riorson, venin, book guide, companion guide, study guide, book club guide.','http://books.google.com/books/content?id=CZCTEQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','2026-03-15 07:00:27','CZCTEQAAQBAJ','A Comprehensive Review and Analysis of the book','Insight Reads Press ',1970,'Fiction','NOT_MATURE','preview-1.0.0',78),(1179,NULL,'Regulations of the United States Naval Academy','United States Naval Academy',NULL,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=c1Re7yS-fi0C&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','2026-03-15 07:00:27','c1Re7yS-fi0C',NULL,NULL,1929,NULL,'NOT_MATURE','4.10.13.0.full.1',194),(1180,'1649376162','Untitled Red Tower 2023 Release',NULL,'New Red Tower Release Coming Soon!','http://books.google.com/books/content?id=pCrcEAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','2026-03-15 07:00:27','pCrcEAAAQBAJ',NULL,'Entangled: Red Tower Books',2023,'Fiction','NOT_MATURE','preview-1.0.0',0),(1181,NULL,'Naval Aviation News',NULL,NULL,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=fmRGAQAAMAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','2026-03-15 07:00:27','fmRGAQAAMAAJ',NULL,NULL,1961,'Aeronautics, Military','NOT_MATURE','1.7.7.0.full.1',1084),(1182,'0231122993','The Mandate of Heaven','S. J. Marshall','The I Ching is one of the cornerstone texts of Chinese civilization and remains a tremendously popular book throughout the world. Scholars have increasingly dismissed the traditions surrounding the text, while many readers in both China and the West have been more willing to accept this divinatory work at face value. S. J. Marshall sets out to reconcile these opposing approaches.','http://books.google.com/books/content?id=QIS-AwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','2026-03-15 07:00:27','QIS-AwAAQBAJ','Hidden History in the I Ching','Columbia University Press',2002,'History','NOT_MATURE','0.2.2.0.preview.1',272),(1183,NULL,'Russell Senate Office Building',NULL,NULL,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=GMijz4t-stYC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','2026-03-15 07:00:27','GMijz4t-stYC','The First Century, 1909-2009',NULL,2009,'Government publications','NOT_MATURE','0.5.7.0.full.1',36),(1184,NULL,'Hearings on Military Posture and H.R. 12564, Department of Defense Authorization for Appropriations for Fiscal Year 1975','United States. Congress. House. Committee on Armed Services',NULL,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=ACwK62RO9xEC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','2026-03-15 07:00:27','ACwK62RO9xEC','Ninety-third Congress, Second Session',NULL,1974,'United States','NOT_MATURE','0.2.2.0.full.1',1918),(1185,NULL,'State of New York Supreme Court Appellate Division Fourth Department',NULL,NULL,'http://books.google.com/books/content?id=EwXe4XPwKA0C&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','2026-03-15 07:00:28','EwXe4XPwKA0C',NULL,NULL,1970,NULL,'NOT_MATURE','0.6.7.0.full.1',1416),(1186,'0593972708','Alchemised','SenLinYu','#1 NEW YORK TIMES BESTSELLER • In this riveting dark fantasy debut, a woman with missing memories fights to survive a war-torn world of necromancy and alchemy—and the man tasked with unearthing the deepest secrets of her past. This stunning hardcover edition features a deluxe jacket with gold foil on the front and a full-color illustration on the reverse, gorgeous designed endpapers, a gold foil case stamp, and, from acclaimed artist Avendell, a black-and-white interior illustration. “What is it you think you’re protecting in that brain of yours? The war is over. Holdfast is dead. The Eternal Flame extinguished. There’s no one left for you to save.” Once a promising alchemist, Helena Marino is now a prisoner—of war and of her own mind. Her Resistance friends and allies have been brutally murdered, her abilities suppressed, and the world she knew destroyed. In the aftermath of a long war, Paladia’s new ruling class of corrupt guild families and depraved necromancers, whose vile undead creatures helped bring about their victory, holds Helena captive. According to Resistance records, she was a healer of little importance within their ranks. But Helena has inexplicable memory loss of the months leading up to her capture, making her enemies wonder: Is she truly as insignificant as she appears, or are her lost memories hiding some vital piece of the Resistance’s final gambit? To uncover the memories buried deep within her mind, Helena is sent to the High Reeve, one of the most powerful and ruthless necromancers in this new world. Trapped on his crumbling estate, Helena’s fight—to protect her lost history and to preserve the last remaining shreds of her former self—is just beginning. For her prison and captor have secrets of their own . . . secrets Helena must unearth, whatever the cost.','http://books.google.com/books/content?id=y0Y_EQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','2026-03-15 07:00:51','y0Y_EQAAQBAJ',NULL,'Random House',2025,'Fiction','NOT_MATURE','1.2.1.0.preview.1',1041),(1187,'8831818384','Alchemised','SenLin Yu','In un mondo intriso di negromanzia e alchimia devastato dalla guerra, una donna senza ricordi combatte per la propria sopravvivenza contro chi vuole portare alla luce i segreti più profondi del suo passato. Un tempo brillante alchimista, Helena Marino è ora una prigioniera di guerra, intrappolata dai suoi carcerieri, ma anche dalla sua stessa mente. I suoi amici e compagni della Resistenza sono stati brutalmente assassinati, le sue abilità annientate e il mondo che conosceva ridotto in cenere. Ora, all\'indomani della lunga guerra, Helena è nelle mani della nuova classe dirigente di Paladia: potenti famiglie di gilde corrotte e spietati negromanti, vittoriosi grazie alla creazione di orrende creature non-morte. Secondo gli archivi della Resistenza, Helena era una guaritrice di scarsa importanza. Tuttavia la sua inspiegabile perdita di memoria nei mesi precedenti la cattura solleva un dubbio inquietante tra i suoi nemici: è davvero così insignificante come sembra, o nei ricordi sepolti della sua mente si nasconde l\'ultima, vitale mossa della Resistenza? Per scoprirlo, Helena viene affidata all\'Alto Reeve, uno dei negromanti più potenti e temuti del nuovo regime. Chiusa nella sua tenuta decadente, dovrà lottare per proteggere la verità e conservare ciò che resta di sé. Ma la sua prigione e il suo aguzzino celano oscuri segreti... segreti che Helena dovrà svelare, a qualunque costo.','http://books.google.com/books/content?id=cJJIEQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','2026-03-15 07:00:51','cJJIEQAAQBAJ',NULL,'Rizzoli',2025,'Fiction','NOT_MATURE','1.6.6.0.preview.3',1040),(1188,NULL,'THE STORY BEHIND THE ALCHEMISED','JAKE BOLOWSKI ','Before you return to Paladia, discover the alchemy that created it. ​Millions have read the story. Now, learn the truth of the legend. ​When Alchemised shattered every record in the publishing world, it left readers with one burning question: Who is SenLinYu? ​In The Story Behind The Alchemised, Jake Bolowski delivers a gripping, novel-styled deep dive into the extraordinary rise of a writer who stayed in the shadows while their words conquered the light. From the rain-drenched forests of Portland to the high-stakes boardrooms of Hollywood, this is the unauthorized account of how a digital ghost became a literary titan. ​Why every fan of the Alchemist needs this biography: ​The Secret History: Discover the real-world inspirations behind the High Reeve and the harrowing magic of Vivimancy. ​The Impossible Journey: How a masterpiece was tapped out on a smartphone in the quiet moments of motherhood, long before the million-dollar deals. ​The Pro-Fiction Revolution: Go inside the movement that changed how we read dark romance and why SenLinYu became its accidental leader. ​The \"Jade Forest\" Exposed: A look at the private philosophy of an author who refuses to be a celebrity, choosing instead to let the work speak for itself. ​Whether you are about to open Alchemised for the first time or you have already memorized every word of Helena and Kaine’s journey, this biography is the essential companion. It is a story of grit, secrecy, and the alchemical process of turning leaden reality into golden fiction. ​The legend is written. The secrets are here.','http://books.google.com/books/content?id=RdLBEQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','2026-03-15 07:00:51','RdLBEQAAQBAJ','AN UNAUTHORIZED NOVEL-STYLED BIOGRAPHY OF SENLINYU','NEWA PUBLISHING COMPANY ',2026,'Biography & Autobiography','NOT_MATURE','preview-1.0.0',49),(1189,'292528261X','Great Dictionary of Atomic Typographic Errors in English. I. Substitution of a Single Letter by Contiguity. Canadian Multilingual Standard. I.1 A-F','Cornéliu Tocan','(21923 lemmata – 26124 Atomic Typographical Errors – 114 pages)','http://books.google.com/books/content?id=22ukEAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','2026-03-15 07:00:51','22ukEAAAQBAJ',NULL,'Créatique',2023,'Reference','NOT_MATURE','0.2.1.0.preview.1',115),(1190,NULL,'Alchemised: No Queda Nadie a Quien Salvar (Spanish Edition)','SenLinYu','En este debut fascinante de dark fantasy, una mujer sin memoria lucha por sobrevivir en un mundo de nigromancia y alquimia devastado por la guerra, mientras se enfrenta con el hombre encargado de desenterrar los secretos más oscuros de su pasado. -¿Qué crees que está protegiendo ese cerebro que tienes? La guerra ha acabado. Holdfast está muerto. La Llama Eterna se ha extinguido. No queda nadie a quien salvar. Helena Marino, alquimista prometedora en el pasado, es ahora una prisionera, de la guerra y de su propia mente. Sus amigos y aliados de la Resistencia han sido brutalmente asesinados, sus habilidades, reprimidas, y el mundo que conocía, destrozado. Tras una larga guerra, la nueva clase dirigente de Paladia, familias corruptas del gremio y nigromantes depravados, cuyos infames no muertos fueron clave para otorgarles la victoria, mantienen cautiva a Helena. Según los registros de la Resistencia, era una curandera insignificante de sus filas. Pero Helena sufre una inexplicable pérdida de memoria que le ha hecho olvidar los meses previos a su cautiverio y que les hace preguntarse a sus enemigos: ¿De verdad es tan insignificante como parece o su pérdida de memoria esconde alguna pieza clave sobre la última táctica de la Resistencia? Para descubrir los recuerdos enterrados en el fondo de su mente, envían a Helena al Inquisidor Supremo, uno de los nigromantes más poderosos y despiadados de este nuevo mundo. Atrapada en su mansión derruida, la lucha de Helena por proteger su historia perdida y preservar los últimos vestigios de la persona que era apenas ha comenzado, pues su cárcel y carcelero esconden sus propios secretos... Secretos que Helena debe desvelar, cueste lo que cueste. ENGLISH DESCRIPTION In this riveting dark fantasy debut, a woman with missing memories fights to survive a war-torn world of necromancy and alchemy--and the man tasked with unearthing the deepest secrets of her past. Once a promising alchemist, Helena Marino is now a prisoner--of war and of her own mind. Her Resistance friends and allies have been brutally murdered, her abilities suppressed, and the world she knew destroyed. In the aftermath of a long war, Paladia\'s new ruling class of corrupt guild families and depraved necromancers whose vile, undead creatures helped bring about their victory, holds Helena captive. According to Resistance records, she was a healer of little importance within their ranks. But Helena has inexplicable memory loss of the months leading up to her capture, making her enemies wonder: Is she truly as insignificant as she appears, or are her lost memories hiding some vital piece of the Resistance\'s final gambit? To uncover the memories buried deep within her mind, Helena is sent to the High Reeve, one of the most powerful and ruthless necromancers in this new world. Trapped on his crumbling estate, Helena\'s fight--to protect her lost history and to preserve the last remaining shreds of her former self--is just beginning. For her prison and captor have secrets of their own . . . secrets Helena must unearth, whatever the cost.','http://books.google.com/books/content?id=64dn0QEACAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','2026-03-15 07:00:51','64dn0QEACAAJ',NULL,'Montena',2025,'Fiction','NOT_MATURE','preview-1.0.0',0),(1191,'9783989780279','Alchemised English Edition','SenLinYu',NULL,NULL,'2026-03-15 07:00:51','tdCt0QEACAAJ','The Global Fantasy Sensation with Sprayed Edges',NULL,2025,NULL,'NOT_MATURE','preview-1.0.0',0),(1192,'1405969687','Alchemised','SenLinYu','***The record-breaking debut and instant Sunday Times Bestseller*** ‘A work of quite staggering ambition. Detailed world-building, intricate plot, Gothic claustrophobia, wraps the readers in its dark embrace’ Daily Mail \'Very readable\' Guardian In a world ruled by necromancers, a woman with missing memories threatens the dark order that keeps her captive - and the man sent to break her. Gothic in tone, epic in scope - this debut is destined to become a modern classic. Once a promising alchemist, Helena Marino is now a prisoner – of war and of her own fractured mind. The Resistance is crushed, her allies dead, her abilities suppressed. The world she knew is gone. Paladia’s corrupt guild families and their necromancer overlords, aided by vile undead creatures now rule - and hold Helena captive. Resistance records claim she was a healer of little importance. Yet, Helena’s inexplicable memory loss makes her enemies wonder: Is she truly insignificant, or do her missing memories conceal the Resistance’s final secret? To uncover the truth, Helena is delivered into the hands of the High Reeve – Paladia’s most feared and merciless necromancer. Trapped on his crumbling estate, she must fight to protect what remains of herself and unearth the secrets buried in her mind, her prison, and her captor . . . whatever the cost. ‘A superb dark fantasy novel set in a war torn world of black magic and alchemy’ Sun','http://books.google.com/books/content?id=rbg3EQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api','2026-03-15 07:00:51','rbg3EQAAQBAJ','The 2025 debut novel phenomenon everyone is talking about and no one can put down','Random House',2025,'Fiction','NOT_MATURE','1.3.3.0.preview.2',1039),(1193,'191239202X','The Complete Dramatic Works of Tang Xianzu','Tang Xianzu','Tang Xianzu (1550–1616) is acclaimed as the \'Shakespeare of the East\' and widely regarded as China\'s greatest playwright, yet his work has not reached Western readers in its entirety. The Complete Dramatic Works of Tang Xianzu represents a literary landmark: this is the first English-language collection of the revered dramatist\'s most important works to be made available outside China. Translated over two decades, the collection showcases the playwright\'s major pieces, including The Purple Flute, The Purple Hairpins, The Nanke Dream, The Handan Dream – and The Peony Pavilion. The Peony Pavilion is the playwright\'s most celebrated work and has drawn comparisons to Homer\'s Odyssey, Virgil\'s Aeneid, Dante\'s Divine Comedy and John Milton\'s Paradise Lost. Known for his lyrical use of metaphor, Tang Xianzu weaves the beauty of nature with the tragedy of emotion. His plays offer an extensive exploration of love, and remain at the heart of Chinese culture. This important collection represents an opportunity for a wider audience to discover the profound and poetic works of this classic playwright.','http://books.google.com/books/content?id=AqpHDwAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&edge=curl&source=gbs_api','2026-03-15 07:00:51','AqpHDwAAQBAJ',NULL,'Bloomsbury Publishing',2018,'Performing Arts','NOT_MATURE','1.2.2.0.preview.1',1068),(1194,NULL,'100 Best Books of 2025 Summaries: Complete Reading Guide','Insight Reads Press','Discover Every Must-Read Book of 2025 — Without Reading 60,000+ Pages Are you drowning in \"must-read\" book recommendations? Struggling to keep up with 2025\'s bestselling books, award winners, and viral book club picks? You\'re not alone. Over 300,000 books published this year. Only 100 truly matter. \"100 Best Books of 2025 Summaries\" is your literary 